
I Love Cake Comments
============================


HTML Tags
-----------------------

1. Replace the use of `<b>` with `<strong>` as it is deprecated.
1. Replace the use of `<i>` with `<em>` as it is deprecated.
1. Don't use `<br /> `too much (or not at all)
1. Always include meta data in `<head>`
1. Keep your html tags lowercase as per HTML5 spec
1. `<ul>` or `<ol>` tags should only contain `<li>` tags

#### Adding more content to lists

Wrong

```html
<ul>
<li>Bundt cakes</li>
<img src="images/cake.jpg">
</ul>
```

Right
```html
<ul>
    <li>
        Bundt cakes
        <img src="images/cake.jpg">
    </li>
</ul>
```


Content
----------------------

1. All content **must** be inside the `<body>` tag
1. Indent your HTML
1. Only have **one** `<h1>` tag per page
1. When linking images make sure the image is publicly accessible (e.g. https://www.omahasteaks.com/gifs/big/d334.jpg)
1. Use any of the `h2-h4` tags for subsection headers instead of `<p><strong>header</strong></p>`
1. Refrain from using any **base64** images
1. Never underline content.

#### Sample base64 image

```html
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," height="350">
```


Assignment
----------------

1. **Do not** include screenshots of your work to prove it works. Your submission will speak for itself if it works or not.
